Hello Ploutos' 😊 Even though I guess everyone of you knows what the word "Book" means but let us agree on it in this notice:

Whenever our TP1 hits, you traders should immediately book half profits made by the trade and lock it = moving SL to our entry point (in case of any reversal occurs later).

If the price is at entry level again after hitting TP1 so the trade automatically closes by itself and so our signal here. Some trades may only hit TP1 while others go to TP2 or TP3.
 
Most important thing is you book after TP1 and lock the trade so we make it safe and secure and the booking procedure repeats itself if waiting for the last TP set by us. 

Nevertheless, it's not obligatory to wait for other TPs if you are not a full time trader so every trader can choose his favorite trading style according to his life and business schedule.


Ploutos Trade Ideas Analyst

Berthe Younes
